 0054:     """
 0055:     Chess engines may send a draw offer after playing its move and may receive
 0056:     one during an offer during its calculations. A draw handler can be used to
 0057:     send, or react to, this information.
 0058: 
 0059:     >>> # Register a standard draw handler.
 0060:     >>> draw_handler = chess.xboard.DrawHandler()
 0061:     >>> engine.draw_handler = draw_handler
 0062: 
 0063:     >>> # Start a search.
 0064:     >>> engine.setboard(board)
 0065:     >>> engine.st(1)
 0066:     >>> engine.go()
 0067:     e2e4
 0068:     offer draw
 0069:     >>>
 0070:     >>> # Do some relevant work.
 0071:     >>> # Check if a draw offer is pending at any given time.
 0072:     >>> draw_handler.pending_offer
 0073:     True
 0074: 
 0075:     See :attr:`~chess.xboard.DrawHandler.pending_offer` for a way to access
 0076:     this flag in a thread-safe way during search.
 0077: 
 0078:     If you want to be notified whenever new information is available,
 0079:     you would usually subclass the :class:`~chess.xboard.DrawHandler` class:
 0080: 
 0081:     >>> class MyHandler(chess.xboard.DrawHandler):
 0082:     ...     def offer_draw(self):
 0083:     ...         # Called whenever offer draw has been processed.
 0084:     ...         super(MyHandler, self).offer_draw()

 0136:     """
 0137:     Chess engines may send information about their calculations if enabled
 0138:     via the *post* command. Post handlers can be used to aggregate or react
 0139:     to this information.
 0140: 
 0141:     >>> # Register a standard post handler.
 0142:     >>> post_handler = chess.xboard.PostHandler()
 0143:     >>> engine.post_handlers.append(post_handler)
 0144: 
 0145:     >>> # Start a search.
 0146:     >>> engine.setboard(board)
 0147:     >>> engine.st(1)
 0148:     >>> engine.go()
 0149:     e2e4
 0150:     >>>
 0151:     >>> # Retrieve the score of the mainline (PV1) after search is completed.
 0152:     >>> # Note that the score is relative to the side to move.
 0153:     >>> post_handler.post["score"]
 0154:     34
 0155: 
 0156:     See :attr:`~chess.xboard.PostHandler.post` for a way to access this dictionary
 0157:     in a thread-safe way during search.
 0158: 
 0159:     If you want to be notified whenever new information is available,
 0160:     you would usually subclass the :class:`~chess.xboard.PostHandler` class:
 0161: 
 0162:     >>> class MyHandler(chess.xboard.PostHandler):
 0163:     ...     def post_info(self):
 0164:     ...         # Called whenever a complete post line has been processed.
